{
  "stem": "2718.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, there were more people who went to school together.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I-- I wouldn't know of anybody who spoke Yiddish at home.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't speak Yiddish at home.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Nor did-- nor do I know of anybody who spoke Yiddish at home.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because my-- my grandparent-- my grandparents from my father's side, they spoke Yiddish at home.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I understood-- I-- yeah, I understood it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And later on, circumstances made me remember it and learn it very quickly again.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But from my mother's side, nobody spoke Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Also religious, also Orthodox, but nobody spoke Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And neither did anybody to my knowledge in the high school, in the gymnasium.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Yiddish was-- was more confined, as I said to you, to the smallest section of very, very ultra-Orthodox Jews, who-- who they-- they didn't have-- they had-- they had a yeshiva, a very big yeshiva.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then, of course, they spoke nothing us but Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yep.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Again, I have to go back-- I have to go back a bit in time.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Up to up to 1940, 1941, the relationship was most amicable.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there was strong friendship between Jews and non-Jews in-- in Budapest.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now, I'll say Budapest because Ujpest and also other suburbs were-- were like-- like great-- great Budapest, great cities.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Like we're talking about 10 kilometers [INAUDIBLE] in the city, [INAUDIBLE] distance.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the relationship was-- was I would say, extremely good, except-- except, of course, when it came to politics.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "When it came to politics, we had the-- we had the party, the Nazi party in-- in Hungary, like everywhere else.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they make no bones about it that they wanted-- what-- what-- what their aim was.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
